    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood of Cedrus libani, having a light brown heartwood and a pungent cedar odor and fairly knotty grain. It is typically used for joinery, garden furniture, gates, fences, and doors.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
